title: Australians rally help for family in Greece over fears of economic collapse
text:
Australians rally help for family in ... Australians rally help for family in Greece over fears of economic collapse Next Story Prev Story 1 hr ago Read more: ABC News 
MARK COLVIN: There are an estimated 600,000 to 700,000 Greek-Australians in Australia, so the fear of a Greek economic collapse has spread its ripples here. Many elderly Greek-Australians are living out their retirement back in their home villages, while some entitled to Greek pensions who live in this country fear being cut off.   ABC News.
